# Maze Game

A top-down 2D maze game built using **SDL3** and **SDL3_ttf/SDL3_image**. Navigate the maze, collect coins, find the key, and reach the exit door to win!

---

Table of Contents

* [Features]
* [Gameplay]
* [Controls]
* [Installation]
* [Assets]
* [Dependencies]
* [License]

---

 Features

* Procedurally generated maze
* Collectible coins with glowing effects
* Key and exit door mechanics
* Player steps and time tracking
* High score tracking (placeholder implementation)
* Neon-style menu buttons with hover effects
* Rules screen for new players
* Game over screen with final score, coins collected, and elapsed time
* Semi-transparent HUD and in-game messages

---

 Gameplay

1. Start the game and enter your name in the menu (default: `Player1`).
2. Click **Play** to view the rules.
3. Navigate the maze using **W/A/S/D** keys.
4. Collect all coins scattered in the maze.
5. Find the **key** to unlock the **door**.
6. Reach the exit door to complete the level.
7. Your score is calculated based on coins collected and time taken.
8. Press **ESC** anytime to return to the main menu.

---

 Controls

| Action           | Key / Mouse |
| ---------------- | ----------- |
| Move Up          | W           |
| Move Down        | S           |
| Move Left        | A           |
| Move Right       | D           |
| Return / Confirm | ENTER       |
| Back / Quit      | ESC         |
| Click buttons    | Mouse       |

---

 Installation

1. Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/maze-game.git
cd maze-game
```

2. Make sure you have **SDL3**, **SDL3_image**, and **SDL3_ttf** installed.

3. Compile the game (example using GCC on Windows):

```bash
gcc main.c -o main.exe -I"C:/Users/Hack3r/Desktop/SDLL/i686-w64-mingw32/include" -I"C:/Users/Hack3r/Desktop/SDL3_image-3.2.4/i686-w64-mingw32/include" -I"C:/Users/Hack3r/Desktop/SDL3_ttf/i686-w64-mingw32/include" -L"C:/Users/Hack3r/Desktop/SDLL/i686-w64-mingw32/lib" -L"C:/Users/Hack3r/Desktop/SDL3_image-3.2.4/i686-w64-mingw32/lib" -L"C:/Users/Hack3r/Desktop/SDL3_ttf/i686-w64-mingw32/lib" -lSDL3 -lSDL3_ttf -lSDL3_image
```

4. Run the executable:

```bash
./main.exe
```

---

 Assets

Place all game assets in an `assets` folder at the same level as the executable:

```
assets/
├── player.png
├── key.png
├── door.png
├── wall.png
├── floor.png
├── coin.png
├── background.png
├── dejavusans.ttf
```

*Make sure all textures and font files exist, otherwise the game will fail to load.*

---

 Dependencies

* SDL3
* SDL3_image
* SDL3_ttf
* Standard C libraries (`stdio.h`, `stdlib.h`, `time.h`, `math.h`)
